claim.claim-text:
1. A curler, comprising:
a body having a longitudinal axis configured so that a section of hair can be wound about the body;
a foot integral with a first axial end of the body, the foot having a surface configured to rest on the scalp; and
an arm is associated with the body, the arm being capable of occupying, by deformation of at least one of the body and the arm, a position in which the arm keeps the section of hair wound around the body;
wherein:
the surface of the foot configured to rest on the scalp has a surface area greater than a surface area of a transverse section through a part of the body about which the section of hair is wound;
the foot comprises means capable of retaining a portion of the section of hair that is not wound about the body;
the arm cooperates with the body to clamp the section of hair between the body and the arm at a clamping location;
the clamping location can be varied to provide a plurality of selectable clamping locations along the body depending upon selective deformation of at least one of the arm and the body;
the body is at least partly toothed; and
a width of the arm is at least as wide as a width of the body including the teeth.

39. A curler, comprising:
a body configured so that a section of hair can be wound about the body, the body including a first end and a second end;
a foot coupled to the body adjacent to said first end; and
an arm associated with the body, the arm cooperating with the body to clamp the section of hair between the body and the arm at a clamping location;
wherein:
the foot comprises a portion extending transversely to the body;
the foot includes a portion that retains a portion of the section of hair that is not wound about the body; and
the clamping location can be varied so that a plurality of said clamping locations can be selected at different locations along the body;
the body is at least partly toothed; and
a width of the arm is at least as wide as a width of the body including the teeth.
